## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Purpose

This FSD specifies the functional changes required to fix the bug where the VS Code extension’s “Download Embedding Model” command fails when the MCP server is not running. Two fixes are specified:

1. **Extension self-contained download** — remove HTTP API dependency, download directly from HuggingFace
2. **ModelRegistry cache invalidation** — re-read registry.json on every access instead of caching at startup

### 1.2 Scope

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Component | Change Type |
| kiro-sdlc-agents/src/model-downloader.ts | Rewrite (self-contained download) |
| mcp-code-intelligence-python/.../model\_registry.py | Modify (cache invalidation) |
| mcp-code-intelligence-nodejs/.../model-registry.ts | Modify (cache invalidation) |
| mcp-code-intelligence-kotlin/.../ModelRegistry.kt | Modify (cache invalidation) |

### 1.3 Definitions

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Term | Definition |
| Self-contained download | Extension downloads model files directly without relying on any external server |
| Cache invalidation | Reading fresh data from disk instead of using in-memory cached copy |
| Registry | JSON file (~/.code-intel/models/registry.json) tracking model state |

