## 3. Use Cases

### 3.1 UC-01: Download Model (Self-Contained)

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Field | Value |
| ID | UC-01 |
| Actor | Developer |
| Precondition | VS Code extension active, internet available |
| Trigger | Developer invokes “Kiro SDLC: Download Embedding Model” |

**Main Flow:**

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Step | Actor | System |
| 1 | Invokes command | — |
| 2 | — | Reads model catalog from hardcoded MODELS constant |
| 3 | — | Reads ~/.code-intel/models/registry.json to determine download/active status |
| 4 | — | Displays QuickPick with models + status icons |
| 5 | Selects model (not downloaded) | — |
| 6 | — | Shows progress notification: “Downloading {name}…” |
| 7 | — | Downloads model.onnx from HuggingFace via HTTPS |
| 8 | — | Downloads vocab file (vocab.txt or sentencepiece.bpe.model) |
| 9 | — | Writes model files to ~/.code-intel/models/{model-name}/ |
| 10 | — | Updates registry.json: adds model entry, sets as active |
| 11 | — | Shows success: “✅ Model downloaded and activated: {name}” |

**Alternative Flows:**

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| ID | Condition | Action |
| AF-01a | Network error during download | Show error: “❌ Download failed: {message}”. Clean up partial files. |
| AF-01b | Model already downloaded | Show option to switch active model (no re-download) |
| AF-01c | Model already active | Show info: “Model is already active” |
| AF-01d | Disk write fails | Show error: “❌ Cannot write model files. Check disk space.” |

**Postcondition:** Model files on disk, registry.json updated, model active

### 3.2 UC-02: Switch Active Model (Self-Contained)

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Field | Value |
| ID | UC-02 |
| Actor | Developer |
| Precondition | Model already downloaded |
| Trigger | Developer selects a downloaded (non-active) model in QuickPick |

**Main Flow:**

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Step | Actor | System |
| 1 | Selects downloaded model | — |
| 2 | — | Asks “Activate this model?” |
| 3 | Confirms | — |
| 4 | — | Updates registry.json: sets active\_model to selected model |
| 5 | — | Shows success: “✅ Active model switched to: {name}” |

**Postcondition:** registry.json updated, MCP server (if running) sees change on next read

### 3.3 UC-03: MCP Server Reads Fresh Registry

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Field | Value |
| ID | UC-03 |
| Actor | MCP Server (internal) |
| Precondition | Server running, registry.json modified externally |
| Trigger | Any code path accesses activeModel or calls getModel() |

**Main Flow:**

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Step | System |
| 1 | Code accesses ModelRegistry.activeModel property |
| 2 | Property getter reads registry.json from disk (no cache) |
| 3 | Parses JSON, returns current active\_model value |

**Key Change:** Previously, registry was read once at construction time and cached. Now, every property access triggers a fresh disk read.

## 4. Business Rules

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| ID | Rule | Change from KSA-104 |
| BR-01 | Extension MUST NOT depend on MCP server for model download | **NEW** — previously required server |
| BR-02 | Extension reads model catalog from local constant (not server API) | **NEW** — previously called /api/models/list |
| BR-03 | Extension writes registry.json directly after download | **NEW** — previously server wrote it |
| BR-04 | ModelRegistry MUST re-read registry.json on every activeModel access | **CHANGED** — previously cached at startup |
| BR-05 | ModelRegistry MUST re-read on every isDownloaded() check | **CHANGED** — previously cached |
| BR-06 | All 3 MCP modules must implement identical cache invalidation | **NEW** |

## 5. Data Specifications

### 5.1 Model Catalog (Hardcoded in Extension)

const MODELS: Record<string, ModelInfo> = {
 "all-MiniLM-L6-v2": {
 displayName: "English (Small, Fast)",
 sizeMb: 90,
 languages: ["en"],
 files: {
 model: "onnx/model.onnx",
 vocab: "vocab.txt"
 },
 baseUrl: "https://huggingface.co/sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2/resolve/main"
 },
 "paraphrase-multilingual-MiniLM-L12-v2": {
 displayName: "Multilingual (50+ languages)",
 sizeMb: 470,
 languages: ["en", "vi", "zh", "ja", "ko", "fr", "de", "es", "ar", "ru"],
 files: {
 model: "onnx/model.onnx",
 vocab: "sentencepiece.bpe.model"
 },
 baseUrl: "https://huggingface.co/sentence-transformers/paraphrase-multilingual-MiniLM-L12-v2/resolve/main"
 }
};

### 5.2 Registry.json (Written by Extension)

Same format as KSA-104 — no schema change:

{
 "active\_model": "all-MiniLM-L6-v2",
 "last\_updated": "2026-05-21T12:00:00Z",
 "models": {
 "all-MiniLM-L6-v2": {
 "path": "~/.code-intel/models/all-MiniLM-L6-v2",
 "downloaded\_at": "2026-05-21T12:00:00Z",
 "size\_bytes": 94371840
 }
 }
}

## 6. Sequence Diagram

### 6.1 Download Flow (After Fix)

![Sequence — Download](data:image/png;base64...) [*Edit in draw.io*](diagrams/sequence-download.drawio)

Developer → Extension: Invoke "Download Embedding Model"
Extension → Extension: Read MODELS catalog (local constant)
Extension → Disk: Read ~/.code-intel/models/registry.json
Extension → Developer: Show QuickPick (models + status)
Developer → Extension: Select model (not downloaded)
Extension → Developer: Show progress notification
Extension → HuggingFace: GET model.onnx (HTTPS direct)
HuggingFace → Extension: Stream file bytes
Extension → Disk: Write ~/.code-intel/models/{name}/model.onnx
Extension → HuggingFace: GET vocab.txt (HTTPS direct)
HuggingFace → Extension: Stream file bytes
Extension → Disk: Write ~/.code-intel/models/{name}/vocab.txt
Extension → Disk: Update registry.json (add model, set active)
Extension → Developer: "✅ Model downloaded and activated"

### 6.2 Cache Invalidation Flow

Extension → Disk: Write registry.json (new model downloaded)
...later...
MCP Server → ModelRegistry: access activeModel property
ModelRegistry → Disk: Read registry.json (FRESH read, no cache)
ModelRegistry → MCP Server: Return new active\_model value

## 7. State Diagram

### 7.1 Extension Download States

![State — Download](data:image/png;base64...) [*Edit in draw.io*](diagrams/state-download.drawio)

States:
- IDLE: Waiting for user command
- SHOWING\_PICKER: QuickPick displayed
- DOWNLOADING: File download in progress
- WRITING\_REGISTRY: Updating registry.json
- SUCCESS: Download complete
- ERROR: Download failed

Transitions:
- IDLE → SHOWING\_PICKER: User invokes command
- SHOWING\_PICKER → DOWNLOADING: User selects model
- SHOWING\_PICKER → IDLE: User cancels
- DOWNLOADING → WRITING\_REGISTRY: Files downloaded successfully
- DOWNLOADING → ERROR: Network/disk error
- WRITING\_REGISTRY → SUCCESS: Registry updated
- ERROR → IDLE: Error shown, user acknowledges
- SUCCESS → IDLE: Success shown

## 8. Error Handling

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Error | Source | User Message | Recovery |
| Network timeout | HuggingFace unreachable | “❌ Download failed: Connection timed out” | Retry manually |
| HTTP 404 | Model URL invalid | “❌ Download failed: Model file not found” | Report bug |
| Disk full | Write fails | “❌ Cannot write model files. Check disk space.” | Free space, retry |
| Permission denied | Directory not writable | “❌ Cannot write to ~/.code-intel/models/” | Fix permissions |
| JSON parse error | Corrupted registry.json | Silently reset to defaults | Auto-recovery |
| Partial download | Interrupted | Clean up partial files, show error | Retry downloads full file |

## 9. Non-Functional Requirements

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| ID | Requirement | Target |
| NFR-01 | Download works without MCP server | 100% — zero server dependency |
| NFR-02 | Registry re-read latency | < 1ms (file < 1KB, OS page cache) |
| NFR-03 | No breaking changes to registry.json format | Backward compatible |
| NFR-04 | All 3 MCP modules updated consistently | Identical behavior |
| NFR-05 | Extension download timeout | 60s per file (configurable) |

## 10. Integration Requirements

### 10.1 Extension → File System

* Write model files to ~/.code-intel/models/{model-name}/
* Write/update registry.json atomically (write temp → rename)
* Create directories if not exist (mkdirSync with recursive: true)

### 10.2 MCP Server → File System

* Read registry.json on every activeModel / isDownloaded() access
* Handle file-not-found gracefully (return defaults)
* Handle JSON parse errors gracefully (return defaults)

